<p>The SOLR schema has following fields:</p>  <pre><code>   &lt;!-- &lt;field name="id" type="string" indexed="true" stored="true" required="true" multiValued="false" /&gt;  --&gt;    &lt;field name="_id" type="string" indexed="true" stored="true" required="true" multiValued="false" /&gt;     &lt;!-- metadata used by mongo-connector --&gt;    &lt;field name="_ts" type="long" indexed="true" stored="true" required="true" multiValued="false" /&gt;    &lt;field name="ns" type="string" indexed="true" stored="true" required="true" multiValued="false" /&gt;       &lt;!-- uncomment the following to ignore any fields that don't already match an existing         field name or dynamic field, rather than reporting them as an error.         alternately, change the type="ignored" to some other type e.g. "text" if you want         unknown fields indexed and/or stored by default --&gt;    &lt;dynamicField name="*" type="ignored" multiValued="true" /&gt;   &lt;!-- Field to use to determine and enforce document uniqueness.       Unless this field is marked with required="false", it will be a required field    --&gt;  &lt;uniqueKey&gt;_id&lt;/uniqueKey&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I am adding the following document:</p>  <blockquote>   <p>{"_id":"change.me","ns":"change.me", "_ts":123}</p> </blockquote>  <p>I get the following error:</p>  <blockquote>   <p>SolrCore org.apache.solr.common.SolrException: Unable to invoke   function processAdd in script: update-script.js:   sun.org.mozilla.javascript.internal.WrappedException: Wrapped   java.lang.NullPointerException (#71) in  at line number 71</p>      <p>SolrDispatchFilter null:org.apache.solr.common.SolrException: Unable   to invoke function processAdd in script: update-script.js:   sun.org.mozilla.javascript.internal.WrappedException: Wrapped   java.lang.NullPointerException (#71) in  at line number 71</p> </blockquote>  <p>What could be the problem? This is SOLR 5.3.0.</p>